Insider Activity


Individual




Leo J. Hindery



Mr. Leo J. Hindery, Jr., is Co-Founder & Managing Partner at InterMedia Advisors LLC. He is on the Board of Directors at Teach For America, Inc.
Prior to co-founding InterMedia Advisors in 2005, Mr. Hindery was Chairman at Yankees Entertainment & Sports Network LLC, Chairman & Chief Executive Officer at GlobalCenter, Inc., President & Chief Executive Officer at AT&T Broadband LLC, an Advisor at Katalyst Ventures, Chief Executive Officer at YankeeNets LLC, and Founder at Telecommunications, Inc. He also served on the board at Options Media Group Holdings, Inc.
Mr. Hindery received his undergraduate degree from Seattle University and an MBA from Stanford University.
Leo Hindery, Jr. served as a director from December 14, 2011 until his resignation on March 16, 2012.  Mr. Hindery advised the Company that his resignation was necessary due to a conflict of interest created by the termination of a potential merger with another company in which he had a continuing position.  Mr. Hindery had been appointed to the Board in anticipation of the potential merger.



